name: Hero Splendor
description: The Splendor is what put most of India on two wheels, and continues to do so in semi-urban and rural areas. It started off as the Hero Honda Splendor in 1994, as a successor to the CD100 and Sleek. It remained in original form for a whole decade, when the Splendor got the first of many cosmetic and styling updates. The Splendor range covers three different capacities – the original 97cc engine that is in production even today, a 110cc engine that was developed and launched after the split with Honda, and a 125cc Super Splendor that caters to those who want more power and torque but don’t need any flashiness.

name: Mahindra Scorpio
description: The Scorpio is one of Mahindra's oldest nameplates in India. It has a bold and boxy design which gives it a menacing look. It comes with a diesel engine mated with a manual gearbox that drives the rear wheels. It is known for its ruggedness and is fairly capable on all types of roads, making it a versatile SUV that can seat up to 7 passengers.

name: Mahindra XUV700​
description: The Mahindra XUV700 is a feature-rich SUV offering a blend of performance, comfort, and advanced technology. It comes with both petrol and diesel engine options, multiple seating configurations, and a host of modern amenities.

name: Mahindra Thar
description: The Mahindra Thar is a compact, rugged SUV designed for both off-road adventures and urban driving. It combines classic design elements with modern features, offering versatility and performance.

name: Hyundai Creta
description: The Hyundai Creta offers a blend of performance and comfort, making it a preferred choice in the compact SUV segment. It comes with multiple engine options, modern design elements, and advanced features suitable for both city and highway driving.

name: Mahindra Thar ROXX
description: The Mahindra Thar Roxx is a 5-door version of the Thar, offering not only two additional doors but also a suite of premium features, different styling elements, excellent off-road capabilities and powerful turbo-petrol and diesel engine options. The Mahindra Thar Roxx 2025 was introduced with minor feature additions that make your life much easier.

name: Tata Punch
description: The Tata Punch is a micro SUV featuring an SUV-inspired design, a spacious cabin, and a host of features. Available in both petrol and CNG variants, the Punch boasts a 5-star safety rating and stands out as a practical choice for those on a budget. An updated Tata Punch 2025 model is expected to be launched with a fresh design later this year.

name: Tata Nexon
description: The Tata Nexon has been among the highest-selling SUVs in India for the last three years and among the most popular choices in the sub-4m SUV segment. With modern looks, revamped interiors and lots of tech, the 2025 Nexon offers a blend of style, comfort, safety, and features that will appeal to those looking for a premium experience in their small family SUV.

name: Hyundai Verna
description: The Hyundai Verna is a compact sedan which is known for its futuristic and unconventional design language, which can be a hit or a miss. The Verna comes loaded with all the features one would expect from a Hyundai and also features level 2 advanced driver assistance systems (ADAS). Apart from a naturally aspirated petrol engine, the Verna also gets the option of a 1.5-litre turbo-petrol engine, which delivers the highest output in its segment.

name: Skoda Slavia
description: The Skoda Slavia is compact sedan with sleek, modern looks and high safety rating. It comfortably seats four passengers and comes well equipped, though interior quality can feel a bit underwhelming. Available with two turbo petrol engine options, the Slavia is known for its sporty performance and fun-to-drive experience, especially with the larger engine of the two. Sportier looking versions of the Slavia like the Monte Carlo and Sportline editions further add to its appeal.

name: Volkswagen Virtus
description: The Volkswagen Virtus, which sports a timeless design in its segment, is known for its fun to drive nature. Equipped with all the necessary modern features, it offers two turbo-petrol engine options, delivering an exhilarating driving experience. The Virtus is perfect for those who prioritize looks and performance above all else.

name: MG Hector
description: The MG Hector is the automaker's debut product in India. It is a mid-size SUV available in a 5-seater layout and is known for its premium design and tech-loaded cabin. It also boasts a large 14-inch touchscreen, connected car technology, and Level 2 ADAS. The Hector is offered in both petrol and diesel engine options.

name: Mahindra Scorpio N
description: The Mahindra Scorpio N is one of the most popular SUVs in India, known for its bold looks, premium features, and powerful petrol and diesel powertrains. An optional four-wheel-drive (4x4) setup is available for those who prefer to take it offroad. The 2025 Mahindra Scorpio N with model year updates is expected later this year with minor feature additions.

name: Mahindra Bolero
description: The Mahindra Bolero is a 7-seater SUV designed to offer a blend of utility and comfort. Its sturdy build and practical features make it a preferred choice for both urban and rural settings.

name: Mahindra BE 6
description: Mahindra BE 6 is a futuristic electric SUV with a sleek design, advanced technology, and powerful performance. It comes with two battery options: 59 kWh offering a range of 535 km and 79 kWh providing up to 682 km. The SUV is equipped with modern features like a 12.3-inch touchscreen, wireless Android Auto & Apple CarPlay, and a panoramic glass roof.

name: Maruti Suzuki Ertiga
description: The Maruti Suzuki Ertiga is a 7-seater Multi-Purpose Vehicle (MPV) known for its spacious interiors, fuel efficiency, and versatility. It is powered by a 1.5-liter K15C Dualjet petrol engine producing 101.64 bhp and 136.8 Nm of torque. Transmission options include a 5-speed manual and a 6-speed automatic. The Ertiga offers features like a 7-inch touchscreen infotainment system, automatic climate control, and multiple safety features.

name: Maruti Suzuki Fronx
description: The Maruti Suzuki Fronx is a subcompact crossover SUV that combines sporty design with practical features. It offers multiple engine options, including a 1.2-liter K-Series Dual Jet Dual VVT petrol engine and a 1.0-liter K10C Boosterjet turbo petrol engine. Transmission choices include a 5-speed manual, 5-speed AMT, and 6-speed automatic. The Fronx is equipped with features like a touchscreen infotainment system, automatic climate control, and advanced safety technologies.

description: Price: Ola S1 Pro price starts at Rs. 1,29,999 (Ex-showroom). The Ola S1 Pro is powered by 8.5kW electric motor, offering a top speed of 116 km/h. The scooter comes with advanced features such as touchscreen display, mobile app connectivity, cruise control, reverse mode, and more. The Ola S1 Pro is one of the most feature-packed electric scooters in its category.

name: Suzuki Avenis 125
description: Price: Suzuki Avenis 125 price starts at Rs. 87,800 (Ex-showroom). The Suzuki Avenis 125 is powered by a 124cc BS6 engine, which produces 8.7 bhp of power and 10 Nm of torque. The scooter comes with a front disc brake and rear drum brake, along with an anti-lock braking system (ABS). It offers a fuel tank capacity of 5.2 liters and weighs around 106 kg. The Avenis 125 is designed for daily commuting with sporty styling and advanced features.

name: Ather 450X
description: Price: Ather 450X price starts at Rs. 1,29,999 (Ex-showroom). The Ather 450X is an electric scooter powered by a 2.9 kWh lithium-ion battery that delivers a top speed of 80 km/h and a range of up to 116 km per charge (ARAI certified). The scooter is equipped with advanced features like a touch screen dashboard, Bluetooth connectivity, and real-time location tracking. It also offers fast charging, where the battery can be charged to 80% in 1 hour.

name: Ola Gig
description: Ola Gig is a smart electric scooter designed for convenience, with a range of features aimed at making the ride more enjoyable and eco-friendly. The scooter comes with a 2.98 kWh battery that delivers a top speed of 80 km/h and offers a range of up to 100 km per charge. It is equipped with multiple ride modes, reverse assist, and fast-charging capabilities.

name: Aprilia SR 160
description: The Aprilia SR 160 is a stylish and high-performance scooter that delivers a sporty riding experience. Powered by a 160cc BS6 engine, it generates a power of 11.0 bhp and a torque of 12.0 Nm. The SR 160 is equipped with telescopic front suspension and monoshock rear suspension. It has a top speed of 115 km/h and comes with disc brakes for superior stopping power. With a weight of 129 kg and a fuel tank capacity of 7 liters, it is a great choice for performance enthusiasts.

name: BharatBenz 1217C
description:
The BharatBenz 1217C is powered by a fuel-efficient 4D34i 4-cylinder 3900cc diesel engine that produces 168 hp (125 kW) at 2500 rpm and 520 Nm at 1500 rpm. Its BS6-compliant engine is mated to a G85 mechanical synchromesh gearbox with 6 forward and 1 reverse gear to ensure seamless gear shifts. 

 

Additionally, it has power take-off (PTO) with a single plate 362 mm dia clutch for delivering power transmission efficiently. Its peak speed at its high-speed gear is 60 kmph to minimise the turnaround time. The foot-operated pneumatic brake is clubbed with the vehicle to deliver high braking force for regulating the vehicle's speed. 

 

The 1217C model has multi-leaf spring suspension at both the front and the rear for jerk-free cargo ride with high payloads. It comes with a fuel tank capacity of 171 litres to move cargo loads effectively for intercity applications. Also, the model has an AdBlue tank of 43 litres to reduce harmful nitrogen oxide emissions from its exhaust.

name: Tata 1512 LPT
description:
The Tata 1512 LPT is powered by a fuel-efficient 3.3L NG BS6 diesel engine that produces 168 hp (125 kW) at 2600 rpm and 390 Nm at 1300-1600 rpm. Its BS6-compliant engine is mated to a G600 6-speed manual gearbox to ensure seamless gear shifts. 

 

Additionally, it has power take-off (PTO) with a single plate 330 mm dia clutch for delivering power transmission efficiently. Its peak speed at its high-speed gear is 80 kmph to minimize the turnaround time. The air brake system is clubbed with the vehicle to deliver high braking force for regulating the vehicle's speed. 

 

The 1512 LPT model has parabolic leaf spring suspension at the front and semi-elliptical leaf springs at the rear for a jerk-free cargo ride with high payloads. It comes with a fuel tank capacity of 160 litres to move cargo loads effectively for intercity applications. Also, the model has an AdBlue tank of 48 litres to reduce harmful nitrogen oxide emissions from its exhaust.

name: Tata Ultra 1918.T
description:
The Tata Ultra 1918.T is powered by a reliable Cummins ISBe 5.6L BS6 diesel engine that produces 180 hp (134 kW) at 2300 rpm and 700 Nm torque at 1200-1800 rpm. The engine is paired with a G750 6-speed manual gearbox, ensuring smooth gear transitions and optimal performance. 

 

Additionally, it features power take-off (PTO) capability and a single-plate 352 mm dia clutch for efficient power transmission. The Tata Ultra 1918.T has a top speed of 80 kmph, making it suitable for long-haul applications. The truck is equipped with air brakes for superior braking performance and safety. 

 

The 1918.T model comes with parabolic leaf spring suspension at the front and semi-elliptical multi-leaf spring suspension at the rear, ensuring a stable and comfortable ride with high payloads. It has a fuel tank capacity of 350 litres, making it suitable for long-distance transportation. Additionally, it features a 48-litre AdBlue tank to comply with BS6 emission norms and reduce nitrogen oxide emissions.

name: BharatBenz 1917R
description:
The BharatBenz 1917R is powered by a reliable OM926 BS6 diesel engine that produces 170 hp (125 kW) at 2500 rpm and 520 Nm torque at 1200-1600 rpm. The engine is paired with a G85 6-speed manual synchromesh gearbox, ensuring smooth gear transitions and optimal performance. 

 

Additionally, it features power take-off (PTO) capability and a single-plate 362 mm dia clutch for efficient power transmission. The BharatBenz 1917R has a top speed of 80 kmph, making it suitable for long-haul applications. The truck is equipped with air brakes for superior braking performance and safety. 

 

The 1917R model comes with multi-leaf spring suspension at the front and rear, ensuring a stable and comfortable ride with high payloads. It has a fuel tank capacity of 215 litres, making it suitable for long-distance transportation. Additionally, it features a 43-litre AdBlue tank to comply with BS6 emission norms and reduce nitrogen oxide emissions.

name: Tata 407 Gold SFC
description:
The Tata 407 Gold SFC is powered by a reliable 4SP BS6 diesel engine that produces 98 hp (73 kW) at 2800 rpm and 300 Nm torque at 1200-2200 rpm. The engine is paired with a G400 5-speed manual gearbox, ensuring smooth gear transitions and optimal performance. 

 

Additionally, it features power take-off (PTO) capability and a single-plate 280 mm dia clutch for efficient power transmission. The Tata 407 Gold SFC has a top speed of 80 kmph, making it suitable for city and intercity transport. The truck is equipped with air brakes for superior braking performance and safety. 

 

The 407 Gold SFC model comes with parabolic leaf spring suspension at the front and semi-elliptical multi-leaf suspension at the rear, ensuring a stable and comfortable ride with high payloads. It has a fuel tank capacity of 60 litres, making it suitable for short- and medium-haul applications. Additionally, it features a 18-litre AdBlue tank to comply with BS6 emission norms and reduce nitrogen oxide emissions.

name: Tata Ace Gold
description:
The Tata Ace Gold is a compact and fuel-efficient mini truck ideal for urban and semi-urban cargo transportation. It is powered by a 2-cylinder, 702 cc, BS6-compliant petrol engine that produces 30 hp (22.5 kW) at 4000 rpm and 55 Nm of torque at 2500-3000 rpm. The engine is paired with a 4-speed manual gearbox for smooth gear shifts and ease of driving. 

 

This mini truck features a single plate dry friction diaphragm type clutch and a sturdy build, making it perfect for last-mile delivery and light-duty cargo applications. It has a top speed of 70 kmph and an excellent turning radius, making it highly maneuverable in tight spaces. 

 

The Tata Ace Gold is equipped with semi-elliptical leaf spring suspension at both the front and rear, providing a smooth ride even on uneven roads. It has a fuel tank capacity of 26 litres and delivers high mileage, making it an economical choice for small businesses and fleet operators.

name: Tata Intra V10
description:
The Tata Intra V10 is a compact and efficient mini truck designed for small business and last-mile delivery needs. It is powered by a 2-cylinder 798 cc BS6-compliant diesel engine that produces 44 hp (33 kW) at 3750 rpm and 110 Nm torque at 1750-2500 rpm. The engine is paired with a 5-speed manual gearbox that ensures smooth and easy shifting. 

 

It features a single plate dry friction diaphragm clutch for reliable power delivery and durability. The Tata Intra V10 offers a top speed of 80 kmph and is built with a strong hydroformed chassis, offering improved structural strength and safety. 

 

The suspension setup includes semi-elliptical leaf springs both at the front and rear, allowing for a stable and comfortable cargo ride. The fuel tank capacity is 30 litres, ideal for city and short-distance haulage. With its compact size and excellent turning radius, it’s a perfect choice for intra-city logistics.

name: Tata Signa 3523.TK
description:
The Tata Signa 3523.TK is a high-performance heavy-duty tipper truck built for demanding construction and mining operations. It is powered by a Cummins ISBe 5.6L BS6-compliant diesel engine that delivers 220 hp (162 kW) at 2300 rpm and 850 Nm of torque at 1000–1600 rpm. The engine is mated to a 6-speed G1150 manual gearbox with a 430 mm single dry plate clutch, ensuring robust and smooth gear transitions under heavy loads. 

 

The Signa 3523.TK has a top speed of 80 kmph and is built on a strong chassis with reinforced frame members for enhanced durability in off-road and rugged environments. It features a heavy-duty bogie suspension at the rear and semi-elliptical leaf springs at the front for optimal ride stability and load handling. 

 

With a 300-litre fuel tank and a 62-litre AdBlue tank, this truck is capable of covering long distances without frequent stops. Its spacious cabin, ergonomic design, and safety features make it ideal for drivers on long and tough routes.

name: Tata Prima 3530.K HRT
description:
The Tata Prima 3530.K HRT is a premium heavy-duty tipper truck designed for tough mining and construction operations. It is powered by a Cummins ISBe 6.7L BS6 diesel engine delivering 300 hp (223 kW) at 2300 rpm and a peak torque of 1100 Nm at 1100–1700 rpm. This engine is mated to a 9-speed Eaton manual gearbox, offering superior power delivery and control in challenging terrain. 

 

The truck features a heavy-duty single plate 430 mm clutch with organic lining and power-assisted hydraulic actuation for enhanced durability and smooth operation. Built with a high-strength chassis, the 3530.K HRT offers exceptional load-bearing capacity and stability. 

 

The front suspension consists of parabolic leaf springs with hydraulic double-acting shock absorbers, while the rear features heavy-duty bogie suspension. A large 300-litre fuel tank and a 62-litre AdBlue tank ensure extended operations without frequent refueling. It also includes a modern Prima cabin with superior ergonomics, AC, and driver-friendly features for maximum comfort on long-duty cycles.

name: Ashok Leyland AVTR 2820 – 6x4
description:
The Ashok Leyland AVTR 2820 – 6x4 is a powerful and versatile tipper truck designed for heavy-duty applications such as construction, mining, and infrastructure projects. It is powered by a 6-cylinder H series 5660 cc BS6 diesel engine that delivers 200 hp (147 kW) at 2400 rpm and 700 Nm torque at 1200–1900 rpm. The engine is coupled with a 6-speed manual synchromesh gearbox, offering smooth performance even under challenging loads. 

 

The truck features a 6x4 axle configuration, making it ideal for off-road and rugged conditions. It comes with a 380 mm single dry plate clutch, a heavy-duty chassis, and durable aggregates to ensure long service life. 

 

The suspension setup includes semi-elliptical leaf springs at the front and NRS-type bogie suspension at the rear. It has a 220-litre fuel tank and a 48-litre AdBlue tank, enabling long-haul operations with fewer fuel stops. The AVTR platform allows modular customization to suit different customer requirements and applications.

name: Mahindra Supro Profit Truck Maxi
description:
The Mahindra Supro Profit Truck Maxi is a compact and fuel-efficient mini truck, ideal for urban logistics, last-mile delivery, and small business transport needs. It is powered by a 2-cylinder 909 cc BS6-compliant diesel engine that delivers 47 hp (35 kW) at 3750 rpm and 100 Nm torque at 1600–3000 rpm. This engine is mated to a 5-speed manual gearbox, offering smooth and economical performance. 

 

The Supro Profit Truck Maxi features a single plate dry clutch, tough suspension, and a robust chassis to handle varying road conditions. With a top speed of 70 kmph and a strong body design, it offers reliability and versatility for day-to-day cargo operations. 

 

The suspension includes 8-leaf springs at the front and 6-leaf springs at the rear to ensure stability and comfort even with full load. It comes with a 33-litre fuel tank and offers a high mileage of around 21 kmpl, making it one of the most cost-effective transport solutions in its category.

name: Mahindra Bolero Maxx Pik-Up (Veero)
description:
The Mahindra Bolero Maxx Pik-Up, popularly known as Veero in some markets, is a rugged and versatile light commercial vehicle tailored for urban and rural cargo transport. It is equipped with a 2.5L m2Di BS6 diesel engine that produces 65 hp (48 kW) at 3200 rpm and 195 Nm of torque at 1400–2200 rpm. The engine is coupled with a 5-speed manual transmission, ensuring efficient power delivery and fuel economy. 

 

Built on a strong ladder-frame chassis, the Veero offers high load-carrying capacity, making it ideal for small businesses, agriculture, and market logistics. It features rigid leaf spring suspension both in the front and rear, providing the strength needed for tough terrains. 

 

It comes with a 45-litre fuel tank and offers impressive mileage, helping reduce running costs. Its cabin is designed with basic driver comfort and reliability in mind. The Mahindra Veero is known for low maintenance, high payload, and a strong resale value in the light commercial vehicle segment.

name: Eicher Pro 2059XP
description:
The Eicher Pro 2059XP is a high-performance light-duty truck ideal for intra-city and last-mile logistics. It is powered by an advanced E474 4-cylinder 2960 cc BS6 diesel engine, which produces 120 hp (90 kW) at 3200 rpm and 350 Nm torque at 1200–2500 rpm. The engine is coupled with a 5-speed manual gearbox for smooth and efficient driveability in urban and semi-urban environments.


The truck is designed with a strong modular chassis, superior cabin comfort, and optimized load body options to cater to diverse transport needs. It features grease-free semi-elliptical laminated leaf springs in the front and rear for better stability and comfort during full-load operations.


It comes equipped with a 60-litre diesel tank and a 24-litre AdBlue tank, supporting long operating hours. With a modern cabin, ergonomic seating, and durable aggregates, the Pro 2059XP ensures a blend of performance, comfort, and profitability for fleet operators and small businesses.

name: Tata Yodha Pickup
description:
The Tata Yodha Pickup is a rugged and reliable light commercial vehicle designed for a variety of load applications, ranging from construction to agriculture and business logistics. It is equipped with a 2.2L BS6 DI diesel engine that delivers 100 hp (75 kW) at 3750 rpm and 250 Nm of torque at 1000–2500 rpm. The vehicle uses a 5-speed manual transmission for smooth power delivery and efficient fuel usage.


Built on a strong body-on-frame chassis, the Yodha features double wishbone front suspension with torsion bar and semi-elliptical leaf springs at the rear for excellent load stability and ride comfort. It has a high payload capacity and comes in multiple configurations to suit different business needs.


The Tata Yodha Pickup includes a 45-litre fuel tank and offers a mileage of approximately 13 kmpl, making it both powerful and economical. It also features stylish design elements, a wide loading area, and a tough front bumper for added durability on rough roads.

name: Kawasaki Z900
description:
The Kawasaki Z900 is a powerful naked street bike that blends aggressive styling with modern performance. It features a 948cc liquid-cooled, inline 4-cylinder BS6 engine that produces 125 hp (92.2 kW) at 9500 rpm and 98.6 Nm of torque at 7700 rpm. The engine is paired with a 6-speed gearbox, offering a refined and thrilling riding experience.


The Z900 comes with a trellis frame, adjustable suspension, and a host of electronic aids like Kawasaki Traction Control (KTRC), power modes, and dual-channel ABS. It sports a TFT color instrument cluster with Bluetooth connectivity via Kawasaki Rideology app for smart functionality.


With aggressive design, sharp LED lighting, and strong road presence, the Z900 is an ideal choice for enthusiasts seeking high-performance and everyday usability. The bike offers excellent ride stability, precise handling, and top-tier braking power with dual front disc brakes and a single rear disc.

name: Kawasaki Ninja H2R
description:
The Kawasaki Ninja H2R is a track-only, hyper-performance motorcycle that represents the pinnacle of engineering and speed. It is powered by a supercharged 998cc inline 4-cylinder, liquid-cooled engine that produces a staggering 310 hp (231 kW), which can reach up to 326 hp (243 kW) with ram air. Torque output stands at 165 Nm at 12500 rpm. 


Mated to a 6-speed dog-ring transmission with Kawasaki Quick Shifter (KQS), the H2R delivers seamless acceleration. It features an aerodynamic carbon fiber winglet-integrated design and trellis frame for extreme high-speed stability.


The Ninja H2R is equipped with state-of-the-art electronics including Kawasaki Launch Control Mode (KLCM), Engine Brake Control, Cornering Management Function (KCMF), and a Bosch IMU. Braking duties are handled by dual 330mm Brembo semi-floating discs with Brembo Stylema calipers at the front.


With ultra-lightweight bodywork and aggressive racing ergonomics, the H2R is designed solely for closed-course riding and is not road legal. It stands as a technological marvel in the world of superbikes.

name: Kawasaki Ninja ZX-10R
description:
The Kawasaki Ninja ZX-10R is a high-performance, race-bred superbike built for both the track and the street. It is equipped with a 998cc liquid-cooled, 4-stroke inline-four BS6-compliant engine that produces 203 hp (149.3 kW) at 13,200 rpm and 114.9 Nm of torque at 11,400 rpm. With RAM air intake, peak power can rise to 213 hp.


The engine is paired with a 6-speed return-type gearbox featuring Kawasaki Quick Shifter (KQS) and a slipper clutch for precise and aggressive riding. The ZX-10R also features advanced electronic rider aids like traction control, launch control, cornering management (KCMF), engine brake control, power modes, and a full TFT digital display with smartphone connectivity.


Suspension duties are handled by Showa Balance Free Front Forks and a horizontal back-link rear suspension. Braking is top-tier with dual 330 mm Brembo discs at the front and a 220 mm disc at the rear.


With its aerodynamic design, integrated winglets, and aggressive riding stance, the Ninja ZX-10R delivers uncompromising performance for superbike enthusiasts.

name: KTM 200 Duke
description:
The KTM 200 Duke is a lightweight and aggressive naked streetfighter, perfect for urban commuting and spirited rides. It features a 199.5cc liquid-cooled, single-cylinder, 4-stroke BS6-compliant engine that produces 25 hp (18.4 kW) at 10,000 rpm and 19.5 Nm of torque at 8000 rpm. 


The engine is mated to a 6-speed transmission that delivers crisp shifts and fast acceleration. The bike is built on a lightweight steel trellis frame and equipped with WP Apex USD front forks and a mono-shock rear suspension for enhanced cornering and comfort.


Braking is handled by a 300 mm front disc and a 230 mm rear disc with single-channel ABS. The 200 Duke also gets a fully digital instrument cluster and an aggressive headlamp design with LED DRLs.


With sharp styling, nimble handling, and an upright riding posture, the KTM 200 Duke is a great choice for beginners and enthusiasts alike.

name: Jawa 42 Bobber
description:
The Jawa 42 Bobber is a uniquely styled factory-custom motorcycle that blends vintage charm with modern engineering. It is powered by a 334cc, single-cylinder, liquid-cooled, fuel-injected BS6 engine that delivers 29.4 hp (21.8 kW) and 32.7 Nm of torque. 


The engine is mated to a smooth 6-speed gearbox and features a slipper clutch for better control. The 42 Bobber stands out with its low-slung single seat, wide handlebars, chopped fenders, and classic round headlamp.


Suspension duties are handled by telescopic forks at the front and a 7-step adjustable mono-shock at the rear. It gets disc brakes on both ends with dual-channel ABS for enhanced safety. The digital instrument cluster, LED lights, and adjustable seat height make it a modern bobber tailored for comfort and aesthetics.


This motorcycle is a great option for those who love relaxed cruising with a touch of retro style and a bold street presence.

name: Jawa 42
description:
The Jawa 42 is a retro-styled modern classic motorcycle known for its elegant design and peppy performance. It is powered by a 294.72cc, single-cylinder, liquid-cooled, fuel-injected BS6 engine that produces 27.3 hp (20.4 kW) and 26.8 Nm of torque. 


The engine is mated to a 6-speed gearbox offering smooth power delivery and improved highway cruising. Its classic round headlamp, offset instrument cluster, bar-end mirrors, and sporty styling give it a distinct presence on the road.


The Jawa 42 comes equipped with telescopic front forks and twin shock absorbers at the rear. It features disc brakes at both ends with dual-channel ABS, ensuring safe and responsive braking. The semi-digital instrument console and comfortable ergonomics make it a favorite among urban and leisure riders.


With a perfect blend of nostalgia and modern technology, the Jawa 42 is a stylish and practical motorcycle for everyday riding.

name: Jawa Perak
description:
The Jawa Perak is a factory-custom bobber motorcycle with an iconic design and a stealthy attitude. It is powered by a 334cc, single-cylinder, liquid-cooled, BS6 engine that generates 30.6 hp (22.9 kW) and 32.7 Nm of torque. 


This engine is paired with a 6-speed gearbox to provide smooth and strong performance across different riding conditions. The Perak features a floating single seat, chopped fenders, and all-black mechanicals that add to its unique low-slung appeal.


Suspension duties are handled by telescopic hydraulic forks in the front and a mono-shock suspension with 7-step preload adjustability at the rear. It comes equipped with disc brakes at both ends with dual-channel ABS for enhanced braking performance.


With its stunning bobber styling and powerful engine, the Jawa Perak is a great choice for riders looking for a bold and distinctive cruiser with a minimalist yet premium look.
